The paper discusses the design of an effective crowdsourcing system for multi-object classification, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of microtasks and aggregation approaches involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of language in speech transcription, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL). The optimization of weights for worker responses involves machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms to deal with greedy workers, which falls under social and information networks (cs.SI).
